<subSubSection id="C3114BE55C48FFC9FF58F853AE17FA24" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C48FFC8FF58F853A9FAF804" blockId="2.[151,1436,1939,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C48FFC8FF58F853AD7DF85B" bold="true" box="[151,273,1939,1964]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dark brown to black, distinctly grey pruinose; frons and face setose; proboscis short; supracervical setae present; scutum with darker longitudinal bands, lateral band tenuous; legs predominantly dark brown; fore tarsomere 1 slightly swollen, subequal to fore tibia width; pterostigma tenuous at apex of costal cell; halter yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C49FFC9FF08FF57AD84FDC2" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,2026]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C49FFC9FF08FF57AD12FF47" bold="true" box="[199,382,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Re-description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="54B0A6CC5C49FFC9FE4AFF58AD98FF47" box="[389,500,152,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Lectotype</typeStatus>
male. Body 4.0 mm; wing 
<quantity id="4CF3B58B5C49FFC9FCE7FF57AF11FF58" box="[808,893,151,175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
long. Head (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FBC0FF57A80DFF58" box="[1039,1121,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Dichoptic. Frons (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FA8DFF57A9FEFF58" box="[1346,1426,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) as wide as ocellar tubercle, slightly higher than greatest width, slightly divergent near antenna, with 6 lateroclinate setae, grey pruinose between setae, matte brown on margin. Face (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FC6CFF1FAF94FF00" box="[931,1016,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) slightly shorter than frons, slightly wider medially, subquadrate, grey pruinose with short distinct slender setae. Palpus yellow, slender, with long clear setae. Proboscis half head height, labrum black, shiny. Ocellar tubercle slightly protruding, ocelli reddish glassy; anterior ocellar seta robust, divergent and 4 shorter distinct posterior setae. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FB9BFE89A8CFFE96" box="[1108,1187,329,353]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) with scape and pedicel yellowish-brown, postpedicel velvety matte black, 1.5X longer than length of scape and pedicel combined, and almost same length as three-segmented stylus. Segment 1 of stylus very short, segment 2 longer, around 0.6 postpedicel length and 4X longer than thin segment 3. Postcranium (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FCA3FE73AFD2FE3C" box="[876,958,435,459]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) brown, densely grey pruinose; upper half with black more robust setae; lower half with clear slender setae; postocular setae short; vertical setae subequal to adjacent setae; occipital seta multiserial and misaligned, upper setae reaching supracervical plate. Gena and postgena with white slender setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C49FFC9FF08FD81ADC1FC82" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,2026]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
Thorax (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FEE7FD81AD10FDAE" box="[296,380,577,601]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Dark brown to black, grey pruinose; postalar lobe light yellowish-brown; scutum with dark longitudinal bands between acrostichal and dorsocentral rows and between dorsocentral and supra-alar rows, lateral band wider, less conspicuous. Chaetotaxy: 3–4 black antepronotals, lateral setae more robust; 1 robust postpronotal, 8–10 slender, with anterior setae clearer; 5–6 white, slender proepisternals; about 15 white, slender proepimerals; uniserial acrostichals distinct in almost complete row, latter setae damaged by pin; uniserial dorsocentrals longer than acrostichals, posterior setae more robust; 3–4 short intra-alar presuturals; 3–4 intra-alar postsuturals in transverse row; 4–5 short aligned supra-alar presuturals; 5 aligned supra-alar postsuturals, penultimate seta robust; 3 robust posterior notopleurals and several anterior slender; 1 postalar; 2 robust scutellars, mixed with short slender intercalary setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C49FFC9FF08FC41AF29FBBD" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,2026]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
Legs (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FEDFFC40ADFAFC6F" box="[272,406,896,920]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Figs 16–18</figureCitation>
). Dark brown with yellow-tinted joints, notably between femora and tibiae. Short setae, some more robust than others. Fore tibia (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FDB9FC64AEA4FC4B" box="[630,712,932,956]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) with row of longer posterodorsal, posterior and posteroventral setae; fore tarsomere 1 slightly swollen, subequal to fore tibia width and about 0.5X length of fore tibia, with apical crown of more robust setae. Mid tibia (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FDA4FC2BAED3FBF4" box="[619,703,1003,1027]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) with 1–2 anteroventral setae and 3 equidistant posteroventral slightly more robust setae. Hind tibia (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FD8BFBCEAEF8FBD1" box="[580,660,1038,1062]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) with 4 anteroventral setae, two distal set closely together, and 1 dorsal placed medially and slightly more robust than other setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C49FFC9FF08FB95A881FB66" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,2026]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
Wing (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FEDBFB95AD05FB9A" box="[276,361,1109,1133]" captionStart="FIGURES 70–75" captionStartId="12.[151,261,579,602]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetId="figure-502@12.[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 70–75. Wings. 70, Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀; 71, H. barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 72, H. carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 73, H. elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂; 74, H. gymnaspis Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 75, H. xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248054/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
). Hyaline with brown veins; base of costal vein with one robust seta (not illustrated in figure); pterostigma tenuous, light brown at apex of costal cell. A 
<subScript id="178F1A2B5C49FFC9FCD7FB48AF4CFB61" attach="left" box="[792,800,1160,1174]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">1</subScript>
evanescent on distal 0.25. Halter yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C49FFC9FF08FB5FA89EFB09" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,2026]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
Abdomen dark brown to black densely grey pruinose in anterior view; dark brown to matte black in dorsal view, grey laterally; setae clear, distinct, lateral setae on basal tergites longer. Tergite 7 with uniserial row of setae posteriorly. Sternites concolorous with tergites. Tergite 8 (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FCEFFB26AF1DFB09" box="[800,881,1254,1278]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) with distinct posterolateral setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C49FFC9FF08FAC9AF53FA7B" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,2026]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
Terminalia (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FE80FAC9ADB4FAD6" box="[335,472,1289,1313]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 11–22" captionStart-1="FIGURES 23–34" captionStartId-0="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionStartId-1="5.[151,261,1390,1413]" captionTargetBox-0="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetBox-1="[165,1424,367,1365]" captionTargetId-0="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetId-1="figure-400@5.[151,1436,359,1370]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionText-0="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." captionText-1="FIGURES 23–34. Hilarempis carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.). 23, head, lateral view; 24, postcranium, posterolateral view; 25, frons, frontal view; 26, thorax, dorsal view; 27, right fore leg, anterior view; 28, right mid leg, anterior view; 29, right hind leg, anterior view; 30, anomaly at vein R4 (paralectotype ♂); 31, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 32, tergite 8, dorsal view; 33, terminalia, lateral view; 34, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 23–26, 27–29, 31 = 0.5 mm; 32–34 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248046" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5248046/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Figs. 19–23</figureCitation>
). In natural position upward-directed and proclinate. Cercus somewhat separated from lobe formed by cercal plate + bacilliform sclerite. Epandrium (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FCA5FAEDAFD1FAB2" box="[874,957,1325,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) suboval, with small dorsal cleft. Hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FF26FA90AD03FA9F" box="[233,367,1360,1384]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Figs. 21–22</figureCitation>
) with lateral apical projection. Postgonite (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C49FFC9FC9DFA90AFCFFA9F" box="[850,931,1360,1384]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="4.[151,261,914,937]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,209,885]" captionTargetId="figure-462@4.[151,1436,195,893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Hilarempis barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. design.). 11, head, lateral view; 12, postcranium, posterolateral view; 13, frons, frontal view; 14, face, frontal view; 15, thorax, dorsal view; 16, left fore leg, posterior view; 17, left mid leg, anterior view; 18, left hind leg, anterior view; 19, terminalia before maceration, lateral view; 20, tergite 8, dorsal view; 21, terminalia, lateral view; 22, terminalia, posterior view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, ce + b scl = cercus + bacilliform sclerite, ej ap = ejaculatory apodeme; ep = epandrium, hypd = hypandrium, ptg = postgonite; ph = phallus. Scale bars: 11–15, 19 = 0.5 mm; 16–18 = 1.0 mm; 20–22 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248044/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) with subapical expansion. Phallus ending at level of postgonite apex. Ejaculatory apodeme lamella-form.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C49FFC9FF08FA57ADF1FA58" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,2026]" box="[199,413,1431,1455]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C49FFC9FF08FA7AAE17FA24" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,2026]" box="[199,635,1466,1491]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C49FFC9FF08FA7AAD83FA24" bold="true" box="[199,495,1466,1491]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" reason="1">Geographic distribution.</emphasis>
